my_not_funk <- function(x) {
  y <- length(x)
  z <- 1
  
  for (i in 1:y) {
    z <- z*x[i]
    
  }
  z
}

my_funky <- function(v, n) {

  
    if (sum(is.na(v))> 0) { v <- gtools::na.replace(v,n)
    v} else {"There is no missing value"}
}

v <- c(1,2,3, 4)

my_funky(v, 5)

my_numeric <- function(x) {
if (is.vector(x) == FALSE) {
    "you must input a vector"
} else if(is.numeric(x) == FALSE) {
    "You must input numeric vector"
  } else if(sum(is.na(x))==0) {
    print(x)
    print("There is no missing value")
  } else {
    x[is.na(x)] <- mean(x, na.rm=TRUE)
    x
  }
}

v <- c(1,2,3,4, 5)
my_numeric(titanic)
## [1] "you must input a vector"

my_character <- function(x) {
if (is.vector(x) == FALSE) {
    "you must input a vector"
} else if(is.character(x) == FALSE) {
    "You must input character vector"
  } else if(sum(is.na(x))==0) {
    print(x)
    print("There is no missing value")
  } else {
    x[is.na(x)] <- names(which.max(table(v)))
    x
  }
}

my_missing <- function(x) {
  
if (is.data.frame(x) == FALSE) {
    "you must input a data frame"
} else if(sum(is.na(x))==0) {
    print(x)
    print("There is no missing value")
  } else {
    x <- x %>% mutate_if(is.numeric, function(x) {
                          x[is.na(x)] <- mean(x, na.rm=TRUE)
                          x
                        })
    x <- x %>% mutate_if(is.character, function(x) {
                        x[is.na(x)] <- names(which.max(table(x)))
                        return(x)

                        }
                )
     
    x
  }
}



c<- my_missing(titanic)

my_character_bar <- function(x, y) {
  if (is.character(x) == 0 | is.character(y) == 0) {
    "Both variables must be character"
  } else {
    a <- cbind(x,y)
    a <- as.data.frame(a)
    names(a) <- c("first", "second")
      ggplot(a, aes(first, fill= second)) +
        geom_bar(position = "dodge")
  }
} 
my_character_bar(titanic$Embarked, titanic$Sex)

less_than_four <- function(x) {
  a <- x %>% mutate_if(is.character, as.factor) %>% select_if(is.factor) %>%
  select_if(~length(levels(.)) <4)

  b <- ceiling(length(names(a))/3)
  par(mfrow=c(b,3))
  
  for (i in seq_along(a)) {
    c <- a[,-i]
    
    for ( j in seq_along(c)) {
      barplot(table(cbind(a[,i], c[,j])), col=c("blue", "red", "yellow"), legend=rownames(table(cbind(a[,i], c[,j]))), beside = TRUE)
      
    }
  }
}

less_than_four(titanic)

func_of_funk <- function(x, k=1, na.rm = TRUE) {
  "Removed NA's"
  if (k == 1) {
    less_than_four(x)
  } else if(k == 2) {
    a <- x %>% select_if(is.numeric)
    b <- names(a)
    c <- list()
    for (i in seq_along(a)) {
      c[[i]] <- ggplot(a, aes_string(b[i])) + geom_density()
    }
    grid.arrange(grobs=c, ncol=3)
  } else if (k ==3) {
    a <- x %>% transmute_if(is.character, as.factor) %>%
                select_if(~length(levels(.))<4)
    a1 <- names(a)
    b <- x %>% select_if(is.numeric)
    b1 <- names(b)
    
    c <- cbind(a,b)
    d <- list()
    for (i in seq_along(b1)) {
      for (j in seq_along(a1)) {
        print(ggplot(c, aes_string(b1[i], col=a1[j])) + geom_density())
      }
    }
  }
  
}

func_of_funk(titanic, k=3)
